ZCZC OE94
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 142300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING A LOW TO THE N OF THE FAEROES MOVS N AND FILLS. THERE
IS ALSO A DPN COMPLEX LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM IN THE MID-ATLANTIC. BY MIDDAY
ON MONDAY THE LOW HAS DEEPENED TO 956 AND LIES IN THE E NERN SECTION.
THROUGH MONDAY AND TUESDAY THE LOW IS SLOW MOV AND REMAINS IN THE MID-ATLANTIC
WITH THE ASSOCIATED FRONTAL SYSTEM MOV E TOWARDS THE UK. THERE IS POTENTIAL
FOR TRANSIENT LOWS TO DEVELOP ALONG THIS FRONT AND MOV N E.
ON WEDNESDAY THE MAIN DEEP LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM IS EXP TO MOV E TOWARDS
THE NW OF THE UK FLN SLTLY. GALES OR NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS ARE EXP TO SPREAD
INTO SHANNON AND ROCKALL ON SUNDAY NIGHT AND THEN SPREAD NE ACROSS THE REST
OF PORTPATRICK THROUGH MONDAY. WINDS GENERALLY EASING ON TUESDAY BUT REMAINING
NEAR GALE ACROSS FAIR ISLE ON TUESDAY EASING LATER. FURTHER STRG OR NEAR
GALE FORCE WINDS ARE POSS ON WEDNESDAY
NNNN